1 //===- MipsConstantIslandPass.cpp - Emit Pc Relative loads ----------------===// ----

7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This pass is used to make Pc relative loads of constants. ----
10 // For now, only Mips16 will use this. ----
11 // ----
12 // Loading constants inline is expensive on Mips16 and it's in general better ----
13 // to place the constant nearby in code space and then it can be loaded with a ----
14 // simple 16 bit load instruction. ----
15 // ----
16 // The constants can be not just numbers but addresses of functions and labels. ----
17 // This can be particularly helpful in static relocation mode for embedded ----
18 // non-linux targets. ----
19 // ----
20 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
21 ----

189 /// MipsConstantIslands - Due to limited PC-relative displacements, Mips ----
190 /// requires constant pool entries to be scattered among the instructions ----
191 /// inside a function. To do this, it completely ignores the normal LLVM ----
192 /// constant pool; instead, it places constants wherever it feels like with ----
193 /// special instructions. ----
194 /// ----
195 /// The terminology used in this pass includes: ----
196 /// Islands - Clumps of constants placed in the function. ----
197 /// Water - Potential places where an island could be formed. ----
198 /// CPE - A constant pool entry that has been placed somewhere, which ----
199 /// tracks a list of users. ----
200 ----
201 class MipsConstantIslands : public MachineFunctionPass { ----
202 /// BasicBlockInfo - Information about the offset and size of a single ----
203 /// basic block. ----
204 struct BasicBlockInfo { ----
205 /// Offset - Distance from the beginning of the function to the beginning ----
206 /// of this basic block. ----
207 /// ----
208 /// Offsets are computed assuming worst case padding before an aligned ----
209 /// block. This means that subtracting basic block offsets always gives a ----
210 /// conservative estimate of the real distance which may be smaller. ----
211 /// ----
212 /// Because worst case padding is used, the computed offset of an aligned ----
213 /// block may not actually be aligned. ----
214 unsigned Offset = 0; ----
215 ----
216 /// Size - Size of the basic block in bytes. If the block contains ----
217 /// inline assembly, this is a worst case estimate. ----
218 /// ----
219 /// The size does not include any alignment padding whether from the ----
220 /// beginning of the block, or from an aligned jump table at the end. ----
221 unsigned Size = 0; ----
222 ----
223 BasicBlockInfo() = default; 0
224 ----
225 unsigned postOffset() const { return Offset + Size; } 0
226 }; ----
227 ----
228 std::vector BBInfo; ----
229 ----
230 /// WaterList - A sorted list of basic blocks where islands could be placed ----
231 /// (i.e. blocks that don't fall through to the following block, due ----
232 /// to a return, unreachable, or unconditional branch). ----
233 std::vector WaterList; ----
234 ----
235 /// NewWaterList - The subset of WaterList that was created since the ----
236 /// previous iteration by inserting unconditional branches. ----
237 SmallSet NewWaterList; ----
238 ----
239 using water_iterator = std::vector::iterator; ----
240 ----
241 /// CPUser - One user of a constant pool, keeping the machine instruction ----
242 /// pointer, the constant pool being referenced, and the max displacement ----
243 /// allowed from the instruction to the CP. The HighWaterMark records the ----
244 /// highest basic block where a new CPEntry can be placed. To ensure this ----
245 /// pass terminates, the CP entries are initially placed at the end of the ----
246 /// function and then move monotonically to lower addresses. The ----
247 /// exception to this rule is when the current CP entry for a particular ----
248 /// CPUser is out of range, but there is another CP entry for the same ----
249 /// constant value in range. We want to use the existing in-range CP ----
250 /// entry, but if it later moves out of range, the search for new water ----
251 /// should resume where it left off. The HighWaterMark is used to record ----
252 /// that point. ----
253 struct CPUser { ----
254 MachineInstr *MI; ----
255 MachineInstr *CPEMI; ----
256 MachineBasicBlock *HighWaterMark; ----
257 ----
258 private: ----
259 unsigned MaxDisp; ----
260 unsigned LongFormMaxDisp; // mips16 has 16/32 bit instructions ----
261 // with different displacements ----
262 unsigned LongFormOpcode; ----
263 ----
264 public: ----
265 bool NegOk; ----
266 ----
267 CPUser(MachineInstr *mi, MachineInstr *cpemi, unsigned maxdisp, 0
268 bool neg, ----
269 unsigned longformmaxdisp, unsigned longformopcode) ----
270 : MI(mi), CPEMI(cpemi), MaxDisp(maxdisp), 0
271 LongFormMaxDisp(longformmaxdisp), LongFormOpcode(longformopcode), 0
272 NegOk(neg){ 0
273 HighWaterMark = CPEMI->getParent(); 0
274 } 0

276 /// getMaxDisp - Returns the maximum displacement supported by MI. ----
277 unsigned getMaxDisp() const { 0
278 unsigned xMaxDisp = ConstantIslandsSmallOffset? 0
279 ConstantIslandsSmallOffset: MaxDisp; 0
280 return xMaxDisp; 0
281 } ----

291 unsigned getLongFormOpcode() const { 0
292 return LongFormOpcode; 0
293 } ----
294 }; ----

312 /// CPEntries - Keep track of all of the constant pool entry machine ----

434 bool MipsConstantIslands::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &mf) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
435 // The intention is for this to be a mips16 only pass for now ----
436 // FIXME: ----
437 MF = &mf; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
438 MCP = mf.getConstantPool(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
439 STI = &mf.getSubtarget(); 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
440 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "constant island machine function " 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
441 << "\n"); ----
442 if (!STI->inMips16Mode() || !MipsSubtarget::useConstantIslands()) { 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
443 return false; 2 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
444 } ----
445 TII = (const Mips16InstrInfo *)STI->getInstrInfo(); 0
446 MFI = MF->getInfo(); 0
447 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "constant island processing " 0
448 << "\n"); ----
449 // ----
450 // will need to make predermination if there is any constants we need to ----
451 // put in constant islands. TBD. ----
452 // ----
453 if (!PrescannedForConstants) prescanForConstants(); 0
454 ----
455 HasFarJump = false; 0
456 // This pass invalidates liveness information when it splits basic blocks. ----
457 MF->getRegInfo().invalidateLiveness(); 0
458 ----
459 // Renumber all of the machine basic blocks in the function, guaranteeing that ----
460 // the numbers agree with the position of the block in the function. ----
461 MF->RenumberBlocks(); 0
462 ----
463 bool MadeChange = false; 0
464 ----
465 // Perform the initial placement of the constant pool entries. To start with, ----
466 // we put them all at the end of the function. ----
467 std::vector CPEMIs; 0
468 if (!MCP->isEmpty()) 0
469 doInitialPlacement(CPEMIs); 0
470 ----
471 /// The next UID to take is the first unused one. ----
472 initPICLabelUId(CPEMIs.size()); 0
473 ----
474 // Do the initial scan of the function, building up information about the ----
475 // sizes of each block, the location of all the water, and finding all of the ----
476 // constant pool users. ----
477 initializeFunctionInfo(CPEMIs); 0
478 CPEMIs.clear(); 0
479 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpBBs()); 0
480 ----
481 /// Remove dead constant pool entries. ----
482 MadeChange |= removeUnusedCPEntries(); 0
483 ----
484 // Iteratively place constant pool entries and fix up branches until there ----
485 // is no change. ----
486 unsigned NoCPIters = 0, NoBRIters = 0; 0
487 (void)NoBRIters; ----
488 while (true) { ----
489 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Beginning CP iteration #" << NoCPIters << '\n'); 0
490 bool CPChange = false; 0
491 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPUsers.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
492 CPChange |= handleConstantPoolUser(i); 0
493 if (CPChange && ++NoCPIters > 30) 0
494 report_fatal_error("Constant Island pass failed to converge!"); 0
495 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpBBs()); 0
496 ----
497 // Clear NewWaterList now. If we split a block for branches, it should ----
498 // appear as "new water" for the next iteration of constant pool placement. ----
499 NewWaterList.clear(); 0
500 ----
501 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Beginning BR iteration #" << NoBRIters << '\n'); 0
502 bool BRChange = false; 0
503 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ImmBranches.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
504 BRChange |= fixupImmediateBr(ImmBranches[i]); 0
505 if (BRChange && ++NoBRIters > 30) 0
506 report_fatal_error("Branch Fix Up pass failed to converge!"); 0
507 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpBBs()); 0
508 if (!CPChange && !BRChange) 0
509 break; 0
510 MadeChange = true; 0
511 } 0
512 ----
513 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << '\n'; dumpBBs()); 0
514 ----
515 BBInfo.clear(); 0
516 WaterList.clear(); 0
517 CPUsers.clear(); 0
518 CPEntries.clear(); 0
519 ImmBranches.clear(); 0
520 return MadeChange; 0
521 } 0

523 /// doInitialPlacement - Perform the initial placement of the constant pool ----
524 /// entries. To start with, we put them all at the end of the function. ----
525 void ----
526 MipsConstantIslands::doInitialPlacement(std::vector &CPEMIs) { 0
527 // Create the basic block to hold the CPE's. ----
528 MachineBasicBlock *BB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(); 0
529 MF->push_back(BB); 0
530 ----
531 // MachineConstantPool measures alignment in bytes. We measure in log2(bytes). ----
532 const Align MaxAlign = MCP->getConstantPoolAlign(); 0
533 ----
534 // Mark the basic block as required by the const-pool. ----
535 // If AlignConstantIslands isn't set, use 4-byte alignment for everything. ----
536 BB->setAlignment(AlignConstantIslands ? MaxAlign : Align(4)); 0
537 ----
538 // The function needs to be as aligned as the basic blocks. The linker may ----
539 // move functions around based on their alignment. ----
540 MF->ensureAlignment(BB->getAlignment()); 0
541 ----
542 // Order the entries in BB by descending alignment. That ensures correct ----
543 // alignment of all entries as long as BB is sufficiently aligned. Keep ----
544 // track of the insertion point for each alignment. We are going to bucket ----
545 // sort the entries as they are created. ----
546 SmallVector InsPoint(Log2(MaxAlign) + 1, 0
547 BB->end()); 0
548 ----
549 // Add all of the constants from the constant pool to the end block, use an ----
550 // identity mapping of CPI's to CPE's. ----
551 const std::vector &CPs = MCP->getConstants(); 0
552 ----
553 const DataLayout &TD = MF->getDataLayout(); 0
554 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPs.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
555 unsigned Size = CPs[i].getSizeInBytes(TD); 0
556 assert(Size >= 4 && "Too small constant pool entry"); 0
557 Align Alignment = CPs[i].getAlign(); 0
558 // Verify that all constant pool entries are a multiple of their alignment. ----
559 // If not, we would have to pad them out so that instructions stay aligned. ----
560 assert(isAligned(Alignment, Size) && "CP Entry not multiple of 4 bytes!"); 0
561 ----
562 // Insert CONSTPOOL_ENTRY before entries with a smaller alignment. ----
563 unsigned LogAlign = Log2(Alignment); 0
564 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsAt = InsPoint[LogAlign]; 0
565 ----
566 MachineInstr *CPEMI = ----
567 BuildMI(*BB, InsAt, DebugLoc(), TII->get(Mips::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY)) 0
568 .addImm(i).addConstantPoolIndex(i).addImm(Size); 0
569 ----
570 CPEMIs.push_back(CPEMI); 0
571 ----
572 // Ensure that future entries with higher alignment get inserted before ----
573 // CPEMI. This is bucket sort with iterators. ----
574 for (unsigned a = LogAlign + 1; a <= Log2(MaxAlign); ++a) 0
575 if (InsPoint[a] == InsAt) 0
576 InsPoint[a] = CPEMI; 0
577 // Add a new CPEntry, but no corresponding CPUser yet. ----
578 CPEntries.emplace_back(1, CPEntry(CPEMI, i)); 0
579 ++NumCPEs; 0
580 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Moved CPI#" << i << " to end of function, size = " 0
581 << Size << ", align = " << Alignment.value() << '\n'); ----
582 } ----
583 LLVM_DEBUG(BB->dump()); 0
584 } 0
585 ----
586 /// BBHasFallthrough - Return true if the specified basic block can fallthrough ----
587 /// into the block immediately after it. ----
588 static bool BBHasFallthrough(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
589 // Get the next machine basic block in the function. ----
590 MachineFunction::iterator MBBI = MBB->getIterator(); 0
591 // Can't fall off end of function. ----
592 if (std::next(MBBI) == MBB->getParent()->end()) 0
593 return false; 0
594 ----
595 MachineBasicBlock *NextBB = &*std::next(MBBI); 0
596 return llvm::is_contained(MBB->successors(), NextBB); 0
597 } ----

599 /// findConstPoolEntry - Given the constpool index and CONSTPOOL_ENTRY MI, ----
600 /// look up the corresponding CPEntry. ----
601 MipsConstantIslands::CPEntry ----
602 *MipsConstantIslands::findConstPoolEntry(unsigned CPI, 0
603 const MachineInstr *CPEMI) { ----
604 std::vector &CPEs = CPEntries[CPI]; 0
605 // Number of entries per constpool index should be small, just do a ----
606 // linear search. ----
607 for (CPEntry &CPE : CPEs) { 0
608 if (CPE.CPEMI == CPEMI) 0
609 return &CPE; 0
610 } ----
611 return nullptr; 0
612 } ----
613 ----
614 /// getCPEAlign - Returns the required alignment of the constant pool entry ----
615 /// represented by CPEMI. Alignment is measured in log2(bytes) units. ----
616 Align MipsConstantIslands::getCPEAlign(const MachineInstr &CPEMI) { 0
617 assert(CPEMI.getOpcode() == Mips::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY); 0
618 ----
619 // Everything is 4-byte aligned unless AlignConstantIslands is set. ----
620 if (!AlignConstantIslands) 0
621 return Align(4); 0
622 ----
623 unsigned CPI = CPEMI.getOperand(1).getIndex(); 0
624 assert(CPI < MCP->getConstants().size() && "Invalid constant pool index."); 0
625 return MCP->getConstants()[CPI].getAlign(); 0
626 } ----
627 ----
628 /// initializeFunctionInfo - Do the initial scan of the function, building up ----
629 /// information about the sizes of each block, the location of all the water, ----
630 /// and finding all of the constant pool users. ----
631 void MipsConstantIslands:: 0
632 initializeFunctionInfo(const std::vector &CPEMIs) { ----
633 BBInfo.clear(); 0
634 BBInfo.resize(MF->getNumBlockIDs()); 0
635 ----
636 // First thing, compute the size of all basic blocks, and see if the function ----
637 // has any inline assembly in it. If so, we have to be conservative about ----
638 // alignment assumptions, as we don't know for sure the size of any ----
639 // instructions in the inline assembly. ----
640 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : *MF) 0
641 computeBlockSize(&MBB); 0
642 ----
643 // Compute block offsets. ----
644 adjustBBOffsetsAfter(&MF->front()); 0
645 ----
646 // Now go back through the instructions and build up our data structures. ----
647 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : *MF) { 0
648 // If this block doesn't fall through into the next MBB, then this is ----
649 // 'water' that a constant pool island could be placed. ----
650 if (!BBHasFallthrough(&MBB)) 0
651 WaterList.push_back(&MBB); 0
652 for (MachineInstr &MI : MBB) { 0
653 if (MI.isDebugInstr()) 0
654 continue; 0
655 ----
656 int Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
657 if (MI.isBranch()) { 0
658 bool isCond = false; 0
659 unsigned Bits = 0; 0
660 unsigned Scale = 1; 0
661 int UOpc = Opc; 0
662 switch (Opc) { 0
663 default: 0
664 continue; // Ignore other branches for now 0
665 case Mips::Bimm16: 0
666 Bits = 11; 0
667 Scale = 2; 0
668 isCond = false; 0
669 break; 0
670 case Mips::BimmX16: 0
671 Bits = 16; 0
672 Scale = 2; 0
673 isCond = false; 0
674 break; 0
675 case Mips::BeqzRxImm16: 0
676 UOpc=Mips::Bimm16; 0
677 Bits = 8; 0
678 Scale = 2; 0
679 isCond = true; 0
680 break; 0
681 case Mips::BeqzRxImmX16: 0
682 UOpc=Mips::Bimm16; 0
683 Bits = 16; 0
684 Scale = 2; 0
685 isCond = true; 0
686 break; 0
687 case Mips::BnezRxImm16: 0
688 UOpc=Mips::Bimm16; 0
689 Bits = 8; 0
690 Scale = 2; 0
691 isCond = true; 0
692 break; 0
693 case Mips::BnezRxImmX16: 0
694 UOpc=Mips::Bimm16; 0
695 Bits = 16; 0
696 Scale = 2; 0
697 isCond = true; 0
698 break; 0
699 case Mips::Bteqz16: 0
700 UOpc=Mips::Bimm16; 0
701 Bits = 8; 0
702 Scale = 2; 0
703 isCond = true; 0
704 break; 0
705 case Mips::BteqzX16: 0
706 UOpc=Mips::Bimm16; 0
707 Bits = 16; 0
708 Scale = 2; 0
709 isCond = true; 0
710 break; 0
711 case Mips::Btnez16: 0
712 UOpc=Mips::Bimm16; 0
713 Bits = 8; 0
714 Scale = 2; 0
715 isCond = true; 0
716 break; 0
717 case Mips::BtnezX16: 0
718 UOpc=Mips::Bimm16; 0
719 Bits = 16; 0
720 Scale = 2; 0
721 isCond = true; 0
722 break; 0
723 } ----
724 // Record this immediate branch. ----
725 unsigned MaxOffs = ((1 << (Bits-1))-1) * Scale; 0
726 ImmBranches.push_back(ImmBranch(&MI, MaxOffs, isCond, UOpc)); 0
727 } ----
728 ----
729 if (Opc == Mips::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY) 0
730 continue; 0
731 ----
732 // Scan the instructions for constant pool operands. ----
733 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) 0
734 if (MO.isCPI()) { 0
735 // We found one. The addressing mode tells us the max displacement ----
736 // from the PC that this instruction permits. ----
737 ----
738 // Basic size info comes from the TSFlags field. ----
739 unsigned Bits = 0; 0
740 unsigned Scale = 1; 0
741 bool NegOk = false; 0
742 unsigned LongFormBits = 0; 0
743 unsigned LongFormScale = 0; 0
744 unsigned LongFormOpcode = 0; 0
745 switch (Opc) { 0
746 default: 0
747 llvm_unreachable("Unknown addressing mode for CP reference!"); 0
748 case Mips::LwRxPcTcp16: 0
749 Bits = 8; 0
750 Scale = 4; 0
751 LongFormOpcode = Mips::LwRxPcTcpX16; 0
752 LongFormBits = 14; 0
753 LongFormScale = 1; 0
754 break; 0
755 case Mips::LwRxPcTcpX16: 0
756 Bits = 14; 0
757 Scale = 1; 0
758 NegOk = true; 0
759 break; 0
760 } ----
761 // Remember that this is a user of a CP entry. ----
762 unsigned CPI = MO.getIndex(); 0
763 MachineInstr *CPEMI = CPEMIs[CPI]; 0
764 unsigned MaxOffs = ((1 << Bits)-1) * Scale; 0
765 unsigned LongFormMaxOffs = ((1 << LongFormBits)-1) * LongFormScale; 0
766 CPUsers.push_back(CPUser(&MI, CPEMI, MaxOffs, NegOk, LongFormMaxOffs, 0
767 LongFormOpcode)); ----
768 ----
769 // Increment corresponding CPEntry reference count. ----
770 CPEntry *CPE = findConstPoolEntry(CPI, CPEMI); 0
771 assert(CPE && "Cannot find a corresponding CPEntry!"); 0
772 CPE->RefCount++; 0
773 ----
774 // Instructions can only use one CP entry, don't bother scanning the ----
775 // rest of the operands. ----
776 break; 0
777 } ----
778 } ----
779 } ----
780 } 0
781 ----
782 /// computeBlockSize - Compute the size and some alignment information for MBB. ----
783 /// This function updates BBInfo directly. ----
784 void MipsConstantIslands::computeBlockSize(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
785 BasicBlockInfo &BBI = BBInfo[MBB->getNumber()]; 0
786 BBI.Size = 0; 0
787 ----
788 for (const MachineInstr &MI : *MBB) 0
789 BBI.Size += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MI); 0
790 } 0
791 ----
792 /// getOffsetOf - Return the current offset of the specified machine instruction ----
793 /// from the start of the function. This offset changes as stuff is moved ----
794 /// around inside the function. ----
795 unsigned MipsConstantIslands::getOffsetOf(MachineInstr *MI) const { 0
796 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
797 ----
798 // The offset is composed of two things: the sum of the sizes of all MBB's ----
799 // before this instruction's block, and the offset from the start of the block ----
800 // it is in. ----
801 unsigned Offset = BBInfo[MBB->getNumber()].Offset; 0
802 ----
803 // Sum instructions before MI in MBB. ----
804 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = MBB->begin(); &*I != MI; ++I) { 0
805 assert(I != MBB->end() && "Didn't find MI in its own basic block?"); 0
806 Offset += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*I); 0
807 } ----
808 return Offset; 0
809 } ----
810 ----
811 /// CompareMBBNumbers - Little predicate function to sort the WaterList by MBB ----
812 /// ID. ----
813 static bool CompareMBBNumbers(const MachineBasicBlock *LHS, 0
814 const MachineBasicBlock *RHS) { ----
815 return LHS->getNumber() < RHS->getNumber(); 0
816 } ----
817 ----
818 /// updateForInsertedWaterBlock - When a block is newly inserted into the ----
819 /// machine function, it upsets all of the block numbers. Renumber the blocks ----
820 /// and update the arrays that parallel this numbering. ----
821 void MipsConstantIslands::updateForInsertedWaterBlock 0
822 (MachineBasicBlock *NewBB) { ----
823 // Renumber the MBB's to keep them consecutive. ----
824 NewBB->getParent()->RenumberBlocks(NewBB); 0
825 ----
826 // Insert an entry into BBInfo to align it properly with the (newly ----
827 // renumbered) block numbers. ----
828 BBInfo.insert(BBInfo.begin() + NewBB->getNumber(), BasicBlockInfo()); 0
829 ----
830 // Next, update WaterList. Specifically, we need to add NewMBB as having ----
831 // available water after it. ----
832 water_iterator IP = llvm::lower_bound(WaterList, NewBB, CompareMBBNumbers); 0
833 WaterList.insert(IP, NewBB); 0
834 } 0
835 ----
836 unsigned MipsConstantIslands::getUserOffset(CPUser &U) const { 0
837 return getOffsetOf(U.MI); 0
838 } ----
839 ----
840 /// Split the basic block containing MI into two blocks, which are joined by ----
841 /// an unconditional branch. Update data structures and renumber blocks to ----
842 /// account for this change and returns the newly created block. ----
843 MachineBasicBlock * ----
844 MipsConstantIslands::splitBlockBeforeInstr(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
845 MachineBasicBlock *OrigBB = MI.getParent(); 0
846 ----
847 // Create a new MBB for the code after the OrigBB. ----
848 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB = ----
849 MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(OrigBB->getBasicBlock()); 0
850 MachineFunction::iterator MBBI = ++OrigBB->getIterator(); 0
851 MF->insert(MBBI, NewBB); 0
852 ----
853 // Splice the instructions starting with MI over to NewBB. ----
854 NewBB->splice(NewBB->end(), OrigBB, MI, OrigBB->end()); 0
855 ----
856 // Add an unconditional branch from OrigBB to NewBB. ----
857 // Note the new unconditional branch is not being recorded. ----
858 // There doesn't seem to be meaningful DebugInfo available; this doesn't ----
859 // correspond to anything in the source. ----
860 BuildMI(OrigBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(Mips::Bimm16)).addMBB(NewBB); 0
861 ++NumSplit; 0
862 ----
863 // Update the CFG. All succs of OrigBB are now succs of NewBB. ----
864 NewBB->transferSuccessors(OrigBB); 0
865 ----
866 // OrigBB branches to NewBB. ----
867 OrigBB->addSuccessor(NewBB); 0
868 ----
869 // Update internal data structures to account for the newly inserted MBB. ----
870 // This is almost the same as updateForInsertedWaterBlock, except that ----
871 // the Water goes after OrigBB, not NewBB. ----
872 MF->RenumberBlocks(NewBB); 0
873 ----
874 // Insert an entry into BBInfo to align it properly with the (newly ----
875 // renumbered) block numbers. ----
876 BBInfo.insert(BBInfo.begin() + NewBB->getNumber(), BasicBlockInfo()); 0
877 ----
878 // Next, update WaterList. Specifically, we need to add OrigMBB as having ----
879 // available water after it (but not if it's already there, which happens ----
880 // when splitting before a conditional branch that is followed by an ----
881 // unconditional branch - in that case we want to insert NewBB). ----
882 water_iterator IP = llvm::lower_bound(WaterList, OrigBB, CompareMBBNumbers); 0
883 MachineBasicBlock* WaterBB = *IP; 0
884 if (WaterBB == OrigBB) 0
885 WaterList.insert(std::next(IP), NewBB); 0
886 else ----
887 WaterList.insert(IP, OrigBB); 0
888 NewWaterList.insert(OrigBB); 0
889 ----
890 // Figure out how large the OrigBB is. As the first half of the original ----
891 // block, it cannot contain a tablejump. The size includes ----
892 // the new jump we added. (It should be possible to do this without ----
893 // recounting everything, but it's very confusing, and this is rarely ----
894 // executed.) ----
895 computeBlockSize(OrigBB); 0
896 ----
897 // Figure out how large the NewMBB is. As the second half of the original ----
898 // block, it may contain a tablejump. ----
899 computeBlockSize(NewBB); 0
900 ----
901 // All BBOffsets following these blocks must be modified. ----
902 adjustBBOffsetsAfter(OrigBB); 0
903 ----
904 return NewBB; 0
905 } ----
906 ----
907 /// isOffsetInRange - Checks whether UserOffset (the location of a constant pool ----
908 /// reference) is within MaxDisp of TrialOffset (a proposed location of a ----
909 /// constant pool entry). ----
910 bool MipsConstantIslands::isOffsetInRange(unsigned UserOffset, 0
911 unsigned TrialOffset, unsigned MaxDisp, ----
912 bool NegativeOK) { ----
913 if (UserOffset <= TrialOffset) { 0
914 // User before the Trial. ----
915 if (TrialOffset - UserOffset <= MaxDisp) 0
916 return true; 0
917 } else if (NegativeOK) { 0
918 if (UserOffset - TrialOffset <= MaxDisp) 0
919 return true; 0
920 } ----
921 return false; 0
922 } ----
923 ----
924 /// isWaterInRange - Returns true if a CPE placed after the specified ----
925 /// Water (a basic block) will be in range for the specific MI. ----
926 /// ----
927 /// Compute how much the function will grow by inserting a CPE after Water. ----
928 bool MipsConstantIslands::isWaterInRange(unsigned UserOffset, 0
929 MachineBasicBlock* Water, CPUser &U, ----
930 unsigned &Growth) { ----
931 unsigned CPEOffset = BBInfo[Water->getNumber()].postOffset(); 0
932 unsigned NextBlockOffset; ----
933 Align NextBlockAlignment; 0
934 MachineFunction::const_iterator NextBlock = ++Water->getIterator(); 0
935 if (NextBlock == MF->end()) { 0
936 NextBlockOffset = BBInfo[Water->getNumber()].postOffset(); 0
937 NextBlockAlignment = Align(1); 0
938 } else { ----
939 NextBlockOffset = BBInfo[NextBlock->getNumber()].Offset; 0
940 NextBlockAlignment = NextBlock->getAlignment(); 0
941 } ----
942 unsigned Size = U.CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
943 unsigned CPEEnd = CPEOffset + Size; 0
944 ----
945 // The CPE may be able to hide in the alignment padding before the next ----
946 // block. It may also cause more padding to be required if it is more aligned ----
947 // that the next block. ----
948 if (CPEEnd > NextBlockOffset) { 0
949 Growth = CPEEnd - NextBlockOffset; 0
950 // Compute the padding that would go at the end of the CPE to align the next ----
951 // block. ----
952 Growth += offsetToAlignment(CPEEnd, NextBlockAlignment); 0
953 ----
954 // If the CPE is to be inserted before the instruction, that will raise ----
955 // the offset of the instruction. Also account for unknown alignment padding ----
956 // in blocks between CPE and the user. ----
957 if (CPEOffset < UserOffset) 0
958 UserOffset += Growth; 0
959 } else ----
960 // CPE fits in existing padding. ----
961 Growth = 0; 0
962 ----
963 return isOffsetInRange(UserOffset, CPEOffset, U); 0
964 } ----
965 ----
966 /// isCPEntryInRange - Returns true if the distance between specific MI and ----
967 /// specific ConstPool entry instruction can fit in MI's displacement field. ----
968 bool MipsConstantIslands::isCPEntryInRange 0
969 (MachineInstr *MI, unsigned UserOffset, ----
970 MachineInstr *CPEMI, unsigned MaxDisp, ----
971 bool NegOk, bool DoDump) { ----
972 unsigned CPEOffset = getOffsetOf(CPEMI); 0
973 ----
974 if (DoDump) { 0
975 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
976 unsigned Block = MI->getParent()->getNumber(); ----
977 const BasicBlockInfo &BBI = BBInfo[Block]; ----
978 dbgs() << "User of CPE#" << CPEMI->getOperand(0).getImm() ----
979 << " max delta=" << MaxDisp ----
980 << format(" insn address=%#x", UserOffset) << " in " ----
981 << printMBBReference(*MI->getParent()) << ": " ----
982 << format("%#x-%x\t", BBI.Offset, BBI.postOffset()) << *MI ----
983 << format("CPE address=%#x offset=%+d: ", CPEOffset, ----
984 int(CPEOffset - UserOffset)); ----
985 }); ----
986 } ----
987 ----
988 return isOffsetInRange(UserOffset, CPEOffset, MaxDisp, NegOk); 0
989 } ----
990 ----
991 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
992 /// BBIsJumpedOver - Return true of the specified basic block's only predecessor ----
993 /// unconditionally branches to its only successor. ----
994 static bool BBIsJumpedOver(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
995 if (MBB->pred_size() != 1 || MBB->succ_size() != 1) 0
996 return false; 0
997 MachineBasicBlock *Succ = *MBB->succ_begin(); 0
998 MachineBasicBlock *Pred = *MBB->pred_begin(); 0
999 MachineInstr *PredMI = &Pred->back(); 0
1000 if (PredMI->getOpcode() == Mips::Bimm16) 0
1001 return PredMI->getOperand(0).getMBB() == Succ; 0
1002 return false; 0
1003 } ----
1004 #endif ----
1005 ----
1006 void MipsConstantIslands::adjustBBOffsetsAfter(MachineBasicBlock *BB) { 0
1007 unsigned BBNum = BB->getNumber(); 0
1008 for(unsigned i = BBNum + 1, e = MF->getNumBlockIDs(); i < e; ++i) { 0
1009 // Get the offset and known bits at the end of the layout predecessor. ----
1010 // Include the alignment of the current block. ----
1011 unsigned Offset = BBInfo[i - 1].Offset + BBInfo[i - 1].Size; 0
1012 BBInfo[i].Offset = Offset; 0
1013 } ----
1014 } 0
1015 ----
1016 /// decrementCPEReferenceCount - find the constant pool entry with index CPI ----
1017 /// and instruction CPEMI, and decrement its refcount. If the refcount ----
1018 /// becomes 0 remove the entry and instruction. Returns true if we removed ----
1019 /// the entry, false if we didn't. ----
1020 bool MipsConstantIslands::decrementCPEReferenceCount(unsigned CPI, 0
1021 MachineInstr *CPEMI) { ----
1022 // Find the old entry. Eliminate it if it is no longer used. ----
1023 CPEntry *CPE = findConstPoolEntry(CPI, CPEMI); 0
1024 assert(CPE && "Unexpected!"); 0
1025 if (--CPE->RefCount == 0) { 0
1026 removeDeadCPEMI(CPEMI); 0
1027 CPE->CPEMI = nullptr; 0
1028 --NumCPEs; 0
1029 return true; 0
1030 } ----
1031 return false; 0
1032 } ----
1033 ----
1034 /// LookForCPEntryInRange - see if the currently referenced CPE is in range; ----
1035 /// if not, see if an in-range clone of the CPE is in range, and if so, ----
1036 /// change the data structures so the user references the clone. Returns: ----
1037 /// 0 = no existing entry found ----
1038 /// 1 = entry found, and there were no code insertions or deletions ----
1039 /// 2 = entry found, and there were code insertions or deletions ----
1040 int MipsConstantIslands::findInRangeCPEntry(CPUser& U, unsigned UserOffset) 0
1041 { ----
1042 MachineInstr *UserMI = U.MI; 0
1043 MachineInstr *CPEMI = U.CPEMI; 0
1044 ----
1045 // Check to see if the CPE is already in-range. ----
1046 if (isCPEntryInRange(UserMI, UserOffset, CPEMI, U.getMaxDisp(), U.NegOk, 0
1047 true)) { ----
1048 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "In range\n"); 0
1049 return 1; 0
1050 } ----
1051 ----
1052 // No. Look for previously created clones of the CPE that are in range. ----
1053 unsigned CPI = CPEMI->getOperand(1).getIndex(); 0
1054 std::vector &CPEs = CPEntries[CPI]; 0
1055 for (CPEntry &CPE : CPEs) { 0
1056 // We already tried this one ----
1057 if (CPE.CPEMI == CPEMI) 0
1058 continue; 0
1059 // Removing CPEs can leave empty entries, skip ----
1060 if (CPE.CPEMI == nullptr) 0
1061 continue; 0
1062 if (isCPEntryInRange(UserMI, UserOffset, CPE.CPEMI, U.getMaxDisp(), 0
1063 U.NegOk)) { 0
1064 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Replacing CPE#" << CPI << " with CPE#" << CPE.CPI 0
1065 << "\n"); ----
1066 // Point the CPUser node to the replacement ----
1067 U.CPEMI = CPE.CPEMI; 0
1068 // Change the CPI in the instruction operand to refer to the clone. ----
1069 for (MachineOperand &MO : UserMI->operands()) 0
1070 if (MO.isCPI()) { 0
1071 MO.setIndex(CPE.CPI); 0
1072 break; 0
1073 } ----
1074 // Adjust the refcount of the clone... ----
1075 CPE.RefCount++; 0
1076 // ...and the original. If we didn't remove the old entry, none of the ----
1077 // addresses changed, so we don't need another pass. ----
1078 return decrementCPEReferenceCount(CPI, CPEMI) ? 2 : 1; 0
1079 } ----
1080 } ----
1081 return 0; 0
1082 } ----
1083 ----
1084 /// LookForCPEntryInRange - see if the currently referenced CPE is in range; ----
1085 /// This version checks if the longer form of the instruction can be used to ----
1086 /// to satisfy things. ----
1087 /// if not, see if an in-range clone of the CPE is in range, and if so, ----
1088 /// change the data structures so the user references the clone. Returns: ----
1089 /// 0 = no existing entry found ----
1090 /// 1 = entry found, and there were no code insertions or deletions ----
1091 /// 2 = entry found, and there were code insertions or deletions ----
1092 int MipsConstantIslands::findLongFormInRangeCPEntry 0
1093 (CPUser& U, unsigned UserOffset) ----
1094 { ----
1095 MachineInstr *UserMI = U.MI; 0
1096 MachineInstr *CPEMI = U.CPEMI; 0
1097 ----
1098 // Check to see if the CPE is already in-range. ----
1099 if (isCPEntryInRange(UserMI, UserOffset, CPEMI, 0
1100 U.getLongFormMaxDisp(), U.NegOk, 0
1101 true)) { ----
1102 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "In range\n"); 0
1103 UserMI->setDesc(TII->get(U.getLongFormOpcode())); 0
1104 U.setMaxDisp(U.getLongFormMaxDisp()); 0
1105 return 2; // instruction is longer length now 0
1106 } ----
1107 ----
1108 // No. Look for previously created clones of the CPE that are in range. ----
1109 unsigned CPI = CPEMI->getOperand(1).getIndex(); 0
1110 std::vector &CPEs = CPEntries[CPI]; 0
1111 for (CPEntry &CPE : CPEs) { 0
1112 // We already tried this one ----
1113 if (CPE.CPEMI == CPEMI) 0
1114 continue; 0
1115 // Removing CPEs can leave empty entries, skip ----
1116 if (CPE.CPEMI == nullptr) 0
1117 continue; 0
1118 if (isCPEntryInRange(UserMI, UserOffset, CPE.CPEMI, U.getLongFormMaxDisp(), 0
1119 U.NegOk)) { 0
1120 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Replacing CPE#" << CPI << " with CPE#" << CPE.CPI 0
1121 << "\n"); ----
1122 // Point the CPUser node to the replacement ----
1123 U.CPEMI = CPE.CPEMI; 0
1124 // Change the CPI in the instruction operand to refer to the clone. ----
1125 for (MachineOperand &MO : UserMI->operands()) 0
1126 if (MO.isCPI()) { 0
1127 MO.setIndex(CPE.CPI); 0
1128 break; 0
1129 } ----
1130 // Adjust the refcount of the clone... ----
1131 CPE.RefCount++; 0
1132 // ...and the original. If we didn't remove the old entry, none of the ----
1133 // addresses changed, so we don't need another pass. ----
1134 return decrementCPEReferenceCount(CPI, CPEMI) ? 2 : 1; 0
1135 } ----
1136 } ----
1137 return 0; 0
1138 } ----
1139 ----
1140 /// getUnconditionalBrDisp - Returns the maximum displacement that can fit in ----
1141 /// the specific unconditional branch instruction. ----
1142 static inline unsigned getUnconditionalBrDisp(int Opc) { 0
1143 switch (Opc) { 0
1144 case Mips::Bimm16: 0
1145 return ((1<<10)-1)*2; 0
1146 case Mips::BimmX16: 0
1147 return ((1<<16)-1)*2; 0
1148 default: 0
1149 break; 0
1150 } ----
1151 return ((1<<16)-1)*2; 0
1152 } ----
1153 ----
1154 /// findAvailableWater - Look for an existing entry in the WaterList in which ----
1155 /// we can place the CPE referenced from U so it's within range of U's MI. ----
1156 /// Returns true if found, false if not. If it returns true, WaterIter ----
1157 /// is set to the WaterList entry. ----
1158 /// To ensure that this pass ----
1159 /// terminates, the CPE location for a particular CPUser is only allowed to ----
1160 /// move to a lower address, so search backward from the end of the list and ----
1161 /// prefer the first water that is in range. ----
1162 bool MipsConstantIslands::findAvailableWater(CPUser &U, unsigned UserOffset, 0
1163 water_iterator &WaterIter) { ----
1164 if (WaterList.empty()) 0
1165 return false; 0
1166 ----
1167 unsigned BestGrowth = ~0u; 0
1168 for (water_iterator IP = std::prev(WaterList.end()), B = WaterList.begin();; 0
1169 --IP) { 0
1170 MachineBasicBlock* WaterBB = *IP; 0
1171 // Check if water is in range and is either at a lower address than the ----
1172 // current "high water mark" or a new water block that was created since ----
1173 // the previous iteration by inserting an unconditional branch. In the ----
1174 // latter case, we want to allow resetting the high water mark back to ----
1175 // this new water since we haven't seen it before. Inserting branches ----
1176 // should be relatively uncommon and when it does happen, we want to be ----
1177 // sure to take advantage of it for all the CPEs near that block, so that ----
1178 // we don't insert more branches than necessary. ----
1179 unsigned Growth; ----
1180 if (isWaterInRange(UserOffset, WaterBB, U, Growth) && 0
1181 (WaterBB->getNumber() < U.HighWaterMark->getNumber() || 0
1182 NewWaterList.count(WaterBB)) && Growth < BestGrowth) { 0
1183 // This is the least amount of required padding seen so far. ----
1184 BestGrowth = Growth; 0
1185 WaterIter = IP; 0
1186 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Found water after " << printMBBReference(*WaterBB) 0
1187 << " Growth=" << Growth << '\n'); ----
1188 ----
1189 // Keep looking unless it is perfect. ----
1190 if (BestGrowth == 0) 0
1191 return true; 0
1192 } ----
1193 if (IP == B) 0
1194 break; 0
1195 } 0
1196 return BestGrowth != ~0u; 0
1197 } ----
1198 ----
1199 /// createNewWater - No existing WaterList entry will work for ----
1200 /// CPUsers[CPUserIndex], so create a place to put the CPE. The end of the ----
1201 /// block is used if in range, and the conditional branch munged so control ----
1202 /// flow is correct. Otherwise the block is split to create a hole with an ----
1203 /// unconditional branch around it. In either case NewMBB is set to a ----
1204 /// block following which the new island can be inserted (the WaterList ----
1205 /// is not adjusted). ----
1206 void MipsConstantIslands::createNewWater(unsigned CPUserIndex, 0
1207 unsigned UserOffset, ----
1208 MachineBasicBlock *&NewMBB) { ----
1209 CPUser &U = CPUsers[CPUserIndex]; 0
1210 MachineInstr *UserMI = U.MI; 0
1211 MachineInstr *CPEMI = U.CPEMI; 0
1212 MachineBasicBlock *UserMBB = UserMI->getParent(); 0
1213 const BasicBlockInfo &UserBBI = BBInfo[UserMBB->getNumber()]; 0
1214 ----
1215 // If the block does not end in an unconditional branch already, and if the ----
1216 // end of the block is within range, make new water there. ----
1217 if (BBHasFallthrough(UserMBB)) { 0
1218 // Size of branch to insert. ----
1219 unsigned Delta = 2; 0
1220 // Compute the offset where the CPE will begin. ----
1221 unsigned CPEOffset = UserBBI.postOffset() + Delta; 0
1222 ----
1223 if (isOffsetInRange(UserOffset, CPEOffset, U)) { 0
1224 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Split at end of " << printMBBReference(*UserMBB) 0
1225 << format(", expected CPE offset %#x\n", CPEOffset)); ----
1226 NewMBB = &*++UserMBB->getIterator(); 0
1227 // Add an unconditional branch from UserMBB to fallthrough block. Record ----
1228 // it for branch lengthening; this new branch will not get out of range, ----
1229 // but if the preceding conditional branch is out of range, the targets ----
1230 // will be exchanged, and the altered branch may be out of range, so the ----
1231 // machinery has to know about it. ----
1232 int UncondBr = Mips::Bimm16; 0
1233 BuildMI(UserMBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(UncondBr)).addMBB(NewMBB); 0
1234 unsigned MaxDisp = getUnconditionalBrDisp(UncondBr); 0
1235 ImmBranches.push_back(ImmBranch(&UserMBB->back(), 0
1236 MaxDisp, false, UncondBr)); ----
1237 BBInfo[UserMBB->getNumber()].Size += Delta; 0
1238 adjustBBOffsetsAfter(UserMBB); 0
1239 return; 0
1240 } ----
1241 } ----
1242 ----
1243 // What a big block. Find a place within the block to split it. ----
1244 ----
1245 // Try to split the block so it's fully aligned. Compute the latest split ----
1246 // point where we can add a 4-byte branch instruction, and then align to ----
1247 // Align which is the largest possible alignment in the function. ----
1248 const Align Align = MF->getAlignment(); 0
1249 unsigned BaseInsertOffset = UserOffset + U.getMaxDisp(); 0
1250 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << format("Split in middle of big block before %#x", 0
1251 BaseInsertOffset)); ----
1252 ----
1253 // The 4 in the following is for the unconditional branch we'll be inserting ----
1254 // Alignment of the island is handled ----
1255 // inside isOffsetInRange. ----
1256 BaseInsertOffset -= 4; 0
1257 ----
1258 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << format(", adjusted to %#x", BaseInsertOffset) 0
1259 << " la=" << Log2(Align) << '\n'); ----
1260 ----
1261 // This could point off the end of the block if we've already got constant ----
1262 // pool entries following this block; only the last one is in the water list. ----
1263 // Back past any possible branches (allow for a conditional and a maximally ----
1264 // long unconditional). ----
1265 if (BaseInsertOffset + 8 >= UserBBI.postOffset()) { 0
1266 BaseInsertOffset = UserBBI.postOffset() - 8; 0
1267 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << format("Move inside block: %#x\n", BaseInsertOffset)); 0
1268 } ----
1269 unsigned EndInsertOffset = BaseInsertOffset + 4 + 0
1270 CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1271 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI = UserMI; 0
1272 ++MI; 0
1273 unsigned CPUIndex = CPUserIndex+1; 0
1274 unsigned NumCPUsers = CPUsers.size(); 0
1275 //MachineInstr *LastIT = 0; ----
1276 for (unsigned Offset = UserOffset + TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*UserMI); 0
1277 Offset < BaseInsertOffset; 0
1278 Offset += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*MI), MI = std::next(MI)) { 0
1279 assert(MI != UserMBB->end() && "Fell off end of block"); 0
1280 if (CPUIndex < NumCPUsers && CPUsers[CPUIndex].MI == MI) { 0
1281 CPUser &U = CPUsers[CPUIndex]; 0
1282 if (!isOffsetInRange(Offset, EndInsertOffset, U)) { 0
1283 // Shift intertion point by one unit of alignment so it is within reach. ----
1284 BaseInsertOffset -= Align.value(); 0
1285 EndInsertOffset -= Align.value(); 0
1286 } ----
1287 // This is overly conservative, as we don't account for CPEMIs being ----
1288 // reused within the block, but it doesn't matter much. Also assume CPEs ----
1289 // are added in order with alignment padding. We may eventually be able ----
1290 // to pack the aligned CPEs better. ----
1291 EndInsertOffset += U.CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1292 CPUIndex++; 0
1293 } ----
1294 } ----
1295 ----
1296 NewMBB = splitBlockBeforeInstr(*--MI); 0
1297 } ----
1298 ----
1299 /// handleConstantPoolUser - Analyze the specified user, checking to see if it ----
1300 /// is out-of-range. If so, pick up the constant pool value and move it some ----
1301 /// place in-range. Return true if we changed any addresses (thus must run ----
1302 /// another pass of branch lengthening), false otherwise. ----
1303 bool MipsConstantIslands::handleConstantPoolUser(unsigned CPUserIndex) { 0
1304 CPUser &U = CPUsers[CPUserIndex]; 0
1305 MachineInstr *UserMI = U.MI; 0
1306 MachineInstr *CPEMI = U.CPEMI; 0
1307 unsigned CPI = CPEMI->getOperand(1).getIndex(); 0
1308 unsigned Size = CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1309 // Compute this only once, it's expensive. ----
1310 unsigned UserOffset = getUserOffset(U); 0
1311 ----
1312 // See if the current entry is within range, or there is a clone of it ----
1313 // in range. ----
1314 int result = findInRangeCPEntry(U, UserOffset); 0
1315 if (result==1) return false; 0
1316 else if (result==2) return true; 0
1317 ----
1318 // Look for water where we can place this CPE. ----
1319 MachineBasicBlock *NewIsland = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(); 0
1320 MachineBasicBlock *NewMBB; ----
1321 water_iterator IP; 0
1322 if (findAvailableWater(U, UserOffset, IP)) { 0
1323 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Found water in range\n"); 0
1324 MachineBasicBlock *WaterBB = *IP; 0
1325 ----
1326 // If the original WaterList entry was "new water" on this iteration, ----
1327 // propagate that to the new island. This is just keeping NewWaterList ----
1328 // updated to match the WaterList, which will be updated below. ----
1329 if (NewWaterList.erase(WaterBB)) 0
1330 NewWaterList.insert(NewIsland); 0
1331 ----
1332 // The new CPE goes before the following block (NewMBB). ----
1333 NewMBB = &*++WaterBB->getIterator(); 0
1334 } else { ----
1335 // No water found. ----
1336 // we first see if a longer form of the instrucion could have reached ----
1337 // the constant. in that case we won't bother to split ----
1338 if (!NoLoadRelaxation) { 0
1339 result = findLongFormInRangeCPEntry(U, UserOffset); 0
1340 if (result != 0) return true; 0
1341 } ----
1342 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "No water found\n"); 0
1343 createNewWater(CPUserIndex, UserOffset, NewMBB); 0
1344 ----
1345 // splitBlockBeforeInstr adds to WaterList, which is important when it is ----
1346 // called while handling branches so that the water will be seen on the ----
1347 // next iteration for constant pools, but in this context, we don't want ----
1348 // it. Check for this so it will be removed from the WaterList. ----
1349 // Also remove any entry from NewWaterList. ----
1350 MachineBasicBlock *WaterBB = &*--NewMBB->getIterator(); 0
1351 IP = llvm::find(WaterList, WaterBB); 0
1352 if (IP != WaterList.end()) 0
1353 NewWaterList.erase(WaterBB); 0
1354 ----
1355 // We are adding new water. Update NewWaterList. ----
1356 NewWaterList.insert(NewIsland); 0
1357 } ----
1358 ----
1359 // Remove the original WaterList entry; we want subsequent insertions in ----
1360 // this vicinity to go after the one we're about to insert. This ----
1361 // considerably reduces the number of times we have to move the same CPE ----
1362 // more than once and is also important to ensure the algorithm terminates. ----
1363 if (IP != WaterList.end()) 0
1364 WaterList.erase(IP); 0
1365 ----
1366 // Okay, we know we can put an island before NewMBB now, do it! ----
1367 MF->insert(NewMBB->getIterator(), NewIsland); 0
1368 ----
1369 // Update internal data structures to account for the newly inserted MBB. ----
1370 updateForInsertedWaterBlock(NewIsland); 0
1371 ----
1372 // Decrement the old entry, and remove it if refcount becomes 0. ----
1373 decrementCPEReferenceCount(CPI, CPEMI); 0
1374 ----
1375 // No existing clone of this CPE is within range. ----
1376 // We will be generating a new clone. Get a UID for it. ----
1377 unsigned ID = createPICLabelUId(); 0
1378 ----
1379 // Now that we have an island to add the CPE to, clone the original CPE and ----
1380 // add it to the island. ----
1381 U.HighWaterMark = NewIsland; 0
1382 U.CPEMI = BuildMI(NewIsland, DebugLoc(), TII->get(Mips::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY)) 0
1383 .addImm(ID).addConstantPoolIndex(CPI).addImm(Size); 0
1384 CPEntries[CPI].push_back(CPEntry(U.CPEMI, ID, 1)); 0
1385 ++NumCPEs; 0
1386 ----
1387 // Mark the basic block as aligned as required by the const-pool entry. ----
1388 NewIsland->setAlignment(getCPEAlign(*U.CPEMI)); 0
1389 ----
1390 // Increase the size of the island block to account for the new entry. ----
1391 BBInfo[NewIsland->getNumber()].Size += Size; 0
1392 adjustBBOffsetsAfter(&*--NewIsland->getIterator()); 0
1393 ----
1394 // Finally, change the CPI in the instruction operand to be ID. ----
1395 for (MachineOperand &MO : UserMI->operands()) 0
1396 if (MO.isCPI()) { 0
1397 MO.setIndex(ID); 0
1398 break; 0
1399 } ----
1400 ----
1401 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1402 dbgs() << " Moved CPE to #" << ID << " CPI=" << CPI ----
1403 << format(" offset=%#x\n", BBInfo[NewIsland->getNumber()].Offset)); ----
1404 ----
1405 return true; 0
1406 } ----

1408 /// removeDeadCPEMI - Remove a dead constant pool entry instruction. Update ----
1409 /// sizes and offsets of impacted basic blocks. ----
1410 void MipsConstantIslands::removeDeadCPEMI(MachineInstr *CPEMI) { 0
1411 MachineBasicBlock *CPEBB = CPEMI->getParent(); 0
1412 unsigned Size = CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1413 CPEMI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1414 BBInfo[CPEBB->getNumber()].Size -= Size; 0
1415 // All succeeding offsets have the current size value added in, fix this. ----
1416 if (CPEBB->empty()) { 0
1417 BBInfo[CPEBB->getNumber()].Size = 0; 0
1418 ----
1419 // This block no longer needs to be aligned. ----
1420 CPEBB->setAlignment(Align(1)); 0
1421 } else { ----
1422 // Entries are sorted by descending alignment, so realign from the front. ----
1423 CPEBB->setAlignment(getCPEAlign(*CPEBB->begin())); 0
1424 } ----
1425 ----
1426 adjustBBOffsetsAfter(CPEBB); 0
1427 // An island has only one predecessor BB and one successor BB. Check if ----
1428 // this BB's predecessor jumps directly to this BB's successor. This ----
1429 // shouldn't happen currently. ----
1430 assert(!BBIsJumpedOver(CPEBB) && "How did this happen?"); 0
1431 // FIXME: remove the empty blocks after all the work is done? ----
1432 } 0

1434 /// removeUnusedCPEntries - Remove constant pool entries whose refcounts ----
1435 /// are zero. ----
1436 bool MipsConstantIslands::removeUnusedCPEntries() { 0
1437 unsigned MadeChange = false; 0
1438 for (std::vector &CPEs : CPEntries) { 0
1439 for (CPEntry &CPE : CPEs) { 0
1440 if (CPE.RefCount == 0 && CPE.CPEMI) { 0
1441 removeDeadCPEMI(CPE.CPEMI); 0
1442 CPE.CPEMI = nullptr; 0
1443 MadeChange = true; 0
1444 } ----
1445 } ----
1446 } ----
1447 return MadeChange; 0
1448 } ----

1450 /// isBBInRange - Returns true if the distance between specific MI and ----
1451 /// specific BB can fit in MI's displacement field. ----
1452 bool MipsConstantIslands::isBBInRange 0
1453 (MachineInstr *MI,MachineBasicBlock *DestBB, unsigned MaxDisp) { ----
1454 unsigned PCAdj = 4; 0
1455 unsigned BrOffset = getOffsetOf(MI) + PCAdj; 0
1456 unsigned DestOffset = BBInfo[DestBB->getNumber()].Offset; 0
1457 ----
1458 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Branch of destination " << printMBBReference(*DestBB) 0
1459 << " from " << printMBBReference(*MI->getParent()) ----
1460 << " max delta=" << MaxDisp << " from " << getOffsetOf(MI) ----
1461 << " to " << DestOffset << " offset " ----
1462 << int(DestOffset - BrOffset) << "\t" << *MI); ----
1463 ----
1464 if (BrOffset <= DestOffset) { 0
1465 // Branch before the Dest. ----
1466 if (DestOffset-BrOffset <= MaxDisp) 0
1467 return true; 0
1468 } else { ----
1469 if (BrOffset-DestOffset <= MaxDisp) 0
1470 return true; 0
1471 } ----
1472 return false; 0
1473 } ----

1475 /// fixupImmediateBr - Fix up an immediate branch whose destination is too far ----
1476 /// away to fit in its displacement field. ----
1477 bool MipsConstantIslands::fixupImmediateBr(ImmBranch &Br) { 0
1478 MachineInstr *MI = Br.MI; 0
1479 unsigned TargetOperand = branchTargetOperand(MI); 0
1480 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = MI->getOperand(TargetOperand).getMBB(); 0
1481 ----
1482 // Check to see if the DestBB is already in-range. ----
1483 if (isBBInRange(MI, DestBB, Br.MaxDisp)) 0
1484 return false; 0
1485 ----
1486 if (!Br.isCond) 0
1487 return fixupUnconditionalBr(Br); 0
1488 return fixupConditionalBr(Br); 0
1489 } ----
1490 ----
1491 /// fixupUnconditionalBr - Fix up an unconditional branch whose destination is ----
1492 /// too far away to fit in its displacement field. If the LR register has been ----
1493 /// spilled in the epilogue, then we can use BL to implement a far jump. ----
1494 /// Otherwise, add an intermediate branch instruction to a branch. ----
1495 bool ----
1496 MipsConstantIslands::fixupUnconditionalBr(ImmBranch &Br) { 0
1497 MachineInstr *MI = Br.MI; 0
1498 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
1499 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = MI->getOperand(0).getMBB(); 0
1500 // Use BL to implement far jump. ----
1501 unsigned BimmX16MaxDisp = ((1 << 16)-1) * 2; 0
1502 if (isBBInRange(MI, DestBB, BimmX16MaxDisp)) { 0
1503 Br.MaxDisp = BimmX16MaxDisp; 0
1504 MI->setDesc(TII->get(Mips::BimmX16)); 0
1505 } ----
1506 else { ----
1507 // need to give the math a more careful look here ----
1508 // this is really a segment address and not ----
1509 // a PC relative address. FIXME. But I think that ----
1510 // just reducing the bits by 1 as I've done is correct. ----
1511 // The basic block we are branching too much be longword aligned. ----
1512 // we know that RA is saved because we always save it right now. ----
1513 // this requirement will be relaxed later but we also have an alternate ----
1514 // way to implement this that I will implement that does not need jal. ----
1515 // We should have a way to back out this alignment restriction ----
1516 // if we "can" later. but it is not harmful. ----
1517 // ----
1518 DestBB->setAlignment(Align(4)); 0
1519 Br.MaxDisp = ((1<<24)-1) * 2; 0
1520 MI->setDesc(TII->get(Mips::JalB16)); 0
1521 } ----
1522 BBInfo[MBB->getNumber()].Size += 2; 0
1523 adjustBBOffsetsAfter(MBB); 0
1524 HasFarJump = true; 0
1525 ++NumUBrFixed; 0
1526 ----
1527 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Changed B to long jump " << *MI); 0
1528 ----
1529 return true; 0
1530 } ----
1531 ----
1532 /// fixupConditionalBr - Fix up a conditional branch whose destination is too ----
1533 /// far away to fit in its displacement field. It is converted to an inverse ----
1534 /// conditional branch + an unconditional branch to the destination. ----
1535 bool ----
1536 MipsConstantIslands::fixupConditionalBr(ImmBranch &Br) { 0
1537 MachineInstr *MI = Br.MI; 0
1538 unsigned TargetOperand = branchTargetOperand(MI); 0
1539 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = MI->getOperand(TargetOperand).getMBB(); 0
1540 unsigned Opcode = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1541 unsigned LongFormOpcode = longformBranchOpcode(Opcode); 0
1542 unsigned LongFormMaxOff = branchMaxOffsets(LongFormOpcode); 0
1543 ----
1544 // Check to see if the DestBB is already in-range. ----
1545 if (isBBInRange(MI, DestBB, LongFormMaxOff)) { 0
1546 Br.MaxDisp = LongFormMaxOff; 0
1547 MI->setDesc(TII->get(LongFormOpcode)); 0
1548 return true; 0
1549 } ----
1550 ----
1551 // Add an unconditional branch to the destination and invert the branch ----
1552 // condition to jump over it: ----
1553 // bteqz L1 ----
1554 // => ----
1555 // bnez L2 ----
1556 // b L1 ----
1557 // L2: ----
1558 ----
1559 // If the branch is at the end of its MBB and that has a fall-through block, ----
1560 // direct the updated conditional branch to the fall-through block. Otherwise, ----
1561 // split the MBB before the next instruction. ----
1562 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
1563 MachineInstr *BMI = &MBB->back(); 0
1564 bool NeedSplit = (BMI != MI) || !BBHasFallthrough(MBB); 0
1565 unsigned OppositeBranchOpcode = TII->getOppositeBranchOpc(Opcode); 0
1566 ----
1567 ++NumCBrFixed; 0
1568 if (BMI != MI) { 0
1569 if (std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)) == std::prev(MBB->end()) && 0
1570 BMI->isUnconditionalBranch()) { 0
1571 // Last MI in the BB is an unconditional branch. Can we simply invert the ----
1572 // condition and swap destinations: ----
1573 // beqz L1 ----
1574 // b L2 ----
1575 // => ----
1576 // bnez L2 ----
1577 // b L1 ----
1578 unsigned BMITargetOperand = branchTargetOperand(BMI); 0
1579 MachineBasicBlock *NewDest = ----
1580 BMI->getOperand(BMITargetOperand).getMBB(); 0
1581 if (isBBInRange(MI, NewDest, Br.MaxDisp)) { 0
1582 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1583 dbgs() << " Invert Bcc condition and swap its destination with " ----
1584 << *BMI); ----
1585 MI->setDesc(TII->get(OppositeBranchOpcode)); 0
1586 BMI->getOperand(BMITargetOperand).setMBB(DestBB); 0
1587 MI->getOperand(TargetOperand).setMBB(NewDest); 0
1588 return true; 0
1589 } ----
1590 } ----
1591 } ----
1592 ----
1593 if (NeedSplit) { 0
1594 splitBlockBeforeInstr(*MI); 0
1595 // No need for the branch to the next block. We're adding an unconditional ----
1596 // branch to the destination. ----
1597 int delta = TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MBB->back()); 0
1598 BBInfo[MBB->getNumber()].Size -= delta; 0
1599 MBB->back().eraseFromParent(); 0
1600 // BBInfo[SplitBB].Offset is wrong temporarily, fixed below ----
1601 } ----
1602 MachineBasicBlock *NextBB = &*++MBB->getIterator(); 0
1603 ----
1604 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Insert B to " << printMBBReference(*DestBB) 0
1605 << " also invert condition and change dest. to " ----
1606 << printMBBReference(*NextBB) << "\n"); ----
1607 ----
1608 // Insert a new conditional branch and a new unconditional branch. ----
1609 // Also update the ImmBranch as well as adding a new entry for the new branch. ----
1610 if (MI->getNumExplicitOperands() == 2) { 0
1611 BuildMI(MBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(OppositeBranchOpcode)) 0
1612 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1613 .addMBB(NextBB); 0
1614 } else { ----
1615 BuildMI(MBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(OppositeBranchOpcode)) 0
1616 .addMBB(NextBB); 0
1617 } ----
1618 Br.MI = &MBB->back(); 0
1619 BBInfo[MBB->getNumber()].Size += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MBB->back()); 0
1620 BuildMI(MBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(Br.UncondBr)).addMBB(DestBB); 0
1621 BBInfo[MBB->getNumber()].Size += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MBB->back()); 0
1622 unsigned MaxDisp = getUnconditionalBrDisp(Br.UncondBr); 0
1623 ImmBranches.push_back(ImmBranch(&MBB->back(), MaxDisp, false, Br.UncondBr)); 0
1624 ----
1625 // Remove the old conditional branch. It may or may not still be in MBB. ----
1626 BBInfo[MI->getParent()->getNumber()].Size -= TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*MI); 0
1627 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1628 adjustBBOffsetsAfter(MBB); 0
1629 return true; 0
1630 } ----

1632 void MipsConstantIslands::prescanForConstants() { 0
1633 unsigned J = 0; 0
1634 (void)J; ----
1635 for (MachineBasicBlock &B : *MF) { 0
1636 for (MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator I = B.instr_begin(), 0
1637 EB = B.instr_end(); 0

1654 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "constant island constant " << *I << "\n"); 0
1655 I->setDesc(TII->get(Mips::LwRxPcTcp16)); 0
